    "description": [
        {
            "text": "Farad Per Meter ($F/m$) is a unit in the category of Electric permittivity. It is also known as farad/meter. This unit is commonly used in the SI unit system. Farad Per Meter has a dimension of M-1L-3T4I2 where $M$ is mass, $L$ is length, $T$ is time, and $I$ is electric current. This unit is the standard SI unit in this category.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
